headline.print_headline: Report Offers a Mixed View of Health Care Law Costs
headline.main: Report Offers a Mixed View of Health Care Law Costs

snippet: The Congressional Budget Office says the overall cost of insurance coverage will be higher than was predicted last year, but much lower than was expected in 2010.
abstract: Congressional Budget Office reports that overall cost of insurance coverage under Affordable Care Act is estimated to be $465 billion in 2016-19, higher than was predicted in 2015, but 25 percent lower than original 2010 estimate.
